author: delawareonline.com
title: Sports dispatches for Wednesday
text:
Wesley’s Callahan earns honors
DOVER Wesley College football senior Joe Callahan was named to the D3football.com Team of the Week after an outstanding performance on Saturday in a 50-49 win over No. 22 North Central College.
Callahan passed for 414 yards and three touchdowns and ran for 111 yards and three more scores.
Goldey-Beacom athletes earn honors
Goldey-Beacom’s Aaron Easter picked CACC men’s cross country Runner of the Week; Pauline Rozet was tabbed to the women’s tennis Weekly Honor Roll.
Easter posted his first career victory on Saturday in capturing the GBC Fall Classic.
Rozet gutted out a thrilling victory Thursday over Stefanie Canals-Bake of Concordia (N.Y.) at fourth singles.
She fought off several match points in an 18-point match tiebreak that went well beyond that to record a 5-7, 6-3, 1-0 (15-13) triumph.
Ryan Lally appointed Delaware Tech athletics coordinator
DOVER Ryan Lally has been appointed Delaware Technical Community College’s athletics coordinator.
In this role, Lally will provide leadership of athletics working with the coaches at each of the campuses to continue the emphasis on academic excellence among student athletes.
Lally will also work closely with the deans of student affairs and campus athletic directors to oversee consistency in planning, implementing and improving athletic programs.
Lally also will be the college’s primary point of contact for recruitment policies, data collection, National Junior College Athletic Association documentation and athletics media outreach plans.
Wilmington women’s soccer win on PK
LAFAYETTE HILL, Pa. A penalty kick with just over 11 minutes left in regulation sent the Wilmington University women’s soccer team to a 1-0 Central Atlantic Collegiate Conference victory at Chestnut Hill.
The Wildcats (4-3, 4-1 CACC) put 19 shots on the board throughout the contest – 12 of which came in the second half, but couldn’t find the back of the net in the first 78 minutes.
A handball in the box proved to be the difference in the contest, as Loran Wyrough buried the opportunity with 11:40 remaining on the game clock.
